-- 
Statoil Creates Advisory Group for Foreign Growth, DN Reports

-- B y   S t e p h e n   T r e l o a r
-- 
2011-04-28T07:08:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/statoil-creates-advisory-group-for-foreign-growth-dn-reports.html
Statoil ASA (STL)  is creating a committee
to advise on its international expansion, Dagens Naeringsliv
 reported , citing spokesman Baard Glad Pedersen.  The Norwegian company has hired David Goldwyn, a former
adviser on energy for the U.S. State Department, as well as
former U.K. MI6 chief John Scarlett and Hassan Marican, the ex-
chief executive officer of Petroliam Nasional Bhd., to sit on
the Strategic Advisory Committee, the Oslo-based newspaper said.
Economist  Joseph Stiglitz  has also been asked to join the
committee, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
